<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-02T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34522/45: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-02T12:00:00-05:00">October 2,
                                    1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>808. Reference my telegram 797, September 28, 4 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d405fn32">Not printed.</note> The Minister of National
                            Defense informed Colonel Montesinos that the President desired to
                            conclude an agreement on the Galápagos within the next few days and
                            before he makes his visit to the United States. Colonel Montesinos has
                            with him a copy of agreement submitted by General Andrews for approval.
                            Request instructions by cable.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Panama for the information of General Andrews.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>